cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as segmentation and localization, which are typically covered under cs.CV. The use of domain adaptation techniques and self-supervised learning suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.LG and cs.AI. The datasets used in the experiments, RobotCar and BDD, are related to robotics and autonomous driving, indicating a possible classification under cs.RO. Finally, the use of machine learning models and techniques suggests a possible classification under cs.NE.
